{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id80b85d04-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3307"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3307"},"text":"§ 3307.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Congressional approval of proposed projects","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id80b85d05-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3307/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Resolutions Required Before Appropriations May Be Made","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The following appropriations may be made only if the Committee on Environment and Public Works of the Senate and the Committee on Transportation and Infrastructure of the House of Representatives adopt resolutions approving the purpose for which the appropriation is made:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id80b85d06-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3307/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" An appropriation to construct, alter, or acquire any building to be used as a public building which involves a total expenditure in excess of $1,500,000, so that the equitable distribution of public buildings throughout the United States with due regard for the comparative urgency of need for the buildings, except as provided in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t40/s3305/b"},"text":"section 3305(b) of this title","children":[],"tail":", is ensured."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id80b85d07-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3307/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" An appropriation to lease any space at an average annual rental in excess of $1,500,000 for use for public purposes.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id80b85d08-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3307/a/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" An appropriation to alter any building, or part of the building, which is under lease by the Federal Government for use for a public purpose if the cost of the alteration will exceed $750,000.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id80b85d09-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3307/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Transmission to Congress of Prospectus of Proposed Project","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"To secure consideration for the approval referred to in subsection (a), the Administrator of General Services (referred to in this section as the “Administrator”) shall transmit to Congress a prospectus of the proposed facility, including—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id80b85d0a-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3307/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a brief description of the building to be constructed, altered, or acquired, or the space to be leased, under this chapter;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id80b85d0b-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3307/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the location of the building or space to be leased and an estimate of the maximum cost to the Government of the facility to be constructed, altered, or acquired, or the space to be leased;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id80b85d0c-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3307/b/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a comprehensive plan for providing space for all Government officers and employees in the locality of the proposed facility or the space to be leased, having due regard for suitable space which may continue to be available in existing Government-owned or occupied buildings, especially those buildings that enhance the architectural, historical, social, cultural, and economic environment of the locality;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id80b85d0d-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3307/b/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" with respect to any project for the construction, alteration, or acquisition of any building, a statement by the Administrator that suitable space owned by the Government is not available and that suitable rental space is not available at a price commensurate with that to be afforded through the proposed action;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id80b85d0e-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3307/b/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a statement by the Administrator of the economic and other justifications for not acquiring a building identified to the Administrator under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t40/s3303/c"},"text":"section 3303(c) of this title","children":[],"tail":" as suitable for the public building needs of the Government;"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id80b85d0f-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3307/b/6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6"},"text":"(6)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a statement of rents and other housing costs currently being paid by the Government for federal agencies to be housed in the building to be constructed, altered, or acquired, or the space to be leased;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id80b85d10-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3307/b/7"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"7"},"text":"(7)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" with respect to any prospectus for the construction, alteration, or acquisition of any building or space to be leased, an estimate of the future energy performance of the building or space and a specific description of the use of energy efficient and renewable energy systems, including photovoltaic systems, in carrying out the project;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id80b85d11-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3307/b/8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"8"},"text":"(8)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a statement of how the proposed project is consistent with the standards and criteria developed under section 11(b) of the Federal Assets Sale and Transfer Act of 2016;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id80b85d12-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3307/b/9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"9"},"text":"(9)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" information on any space occupied by the relevant agency in the geographical area of the proposed facility, including uses, utilization rates, any proposed consolidations, and, if not proposed to be consolidated, a justification for such determination;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id80b85d13-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3307/b/10"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"10"},"text":"(10)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a statement by the Administrator of whether the public building needs of the Government for the proposed space to be leased were formerly met by a federally owned building, including any building identified for disposal or sale; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id80b85d14-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3307/b/11"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"11"},"text":"(11)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" details on actual utilization rates, including number of personnel assigned to the facility, number of personnel expected to work in-person at the facility and whether all personnel identified reflect filled and authorized positions.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id80b85d15-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3307/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Increase of Estimated Maximum Cost","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The estimated maximum cost of any project approved under this section as set forth in any prospectus may be increased by an amount equal to any percentage increase, as determined by the Administrator, in construction or alteration costs from the date the prospectus is transmitted to Congress. The increase authorized by this subsection may not exceed 10 percent of the estimated maximum cost. The Administrator shall notify, in writing, the Committee on Transportation and Infrastructure of the House of Representatives and the Committee on Environment and Public Works of the Senate of any increase of more than 5 percent of an estimated maximum cost or of any increase or decrease in the scope or size of a project of 5 or more percent. Such notification shall include an explanation regarding any such increase or decrease. The scope or size of a project shall not increase or decrease by more than 10 percent unless an amended prospectus is submitted and approved pursuant to this section.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id80b85d16-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3307/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Rescission of Approval","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"If an appropriation is not made within one year after the date a project for construction, alteration, or acquisition is approved under subsection (a), the Committee on Environment and Public Works of the Senate or the Committee on Transportation and Infrastructure of the House of Representatives by resolution may rescind its approval before an appropriation is made.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id80b85d17-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3307/e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Emergency Leases by the Administrator","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"This section does not prevent the Administrator from entering into emergency leases during any period declared by the President to require emergency leasing authority. An emergency lease may not be for more than 180 days without approval of a prospectus for the lease in accordance with subsection (a).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id80b85d18-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3307/f"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"f"},"text":"(f)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Minimum Performance Requirements for Leased Space","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"With respect to space to be leased, the Administrator shall include, to the maximum extent practicable, minimum performance requirements requiring energy efficiency and the use of renewable energy.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id80b85d19-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3307/g"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"g"},"text":"(g)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Limitation on Leasing Certain Space.—","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id80b85d1a-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3307/g/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"In general","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The Administrator may not lease space to accommodate any of the following if the average rental cost of leasing the space will exceed $1,500,000:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id80b85d1b-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3307/g/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Computer and telecommunications operations.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id80b85d1c-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3307/g/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Secure or sensitive activities related to the national defense or security, except when it would be inappropriate to locate those activities in a public building or other facility identified with the Government.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id80b85d1d-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3307/g/1/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" A permanent courtroom, judicial chamber, or administrative office for any United States court.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id80b85d1e-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3307/g/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Exception","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The Administrator may lease space with respect to which paragraph (1) applies if the Administrator—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id80b85d1f-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3307/g/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" decides, for reasons set forth in writing, that leasing the space is necessary to meet requirements which cannot be met in public buildings; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id80b85d20-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3307/g/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" submits the reasons to the Committee on Environment and Public Works of the Senate and the Committee on Transportation and Infrastructure of the House of Representatives.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id80b85d21-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3307/h"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"h"},"text":"(h)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Dollar Amount Adjustment","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The Administrator annually may adjust any dollar amount referred to in this section to reflect a percentage increase or decrease in construction costs during the prior calendar year, as determined by the composite index of construction costs of the Department of Commerce. Any adjustment shall be expeditiously reported to the Committee on Environment and Public Works of the Senate and the Committee on Transportation and Infrastructure of the House of Representatives.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id80b85d22-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3307/i"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Notification Required","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"For each project approved under this section, the Administrator shall notify, in writing, the Committee on Transportation and Infrastructure of the House of Representatives and the Committee on Environment and Public Works of the Senate of any project milestones that are accomplished, including—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id80b85d23-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3307/i/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the solicitation and award of design and construction services;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id80b85d24-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3307/i/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the completion of any actions required for the project pursuant to the National Environmental Policy Act of 1969 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s4321"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 4321","children":[],"tail":" et seq.);"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id80b85d25-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3307/i/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" any ceremonies for the beginning or completion of the project;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id80b85d26-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3307/i/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a naming ceremony for the project; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id80b85d27-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3307/i/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the completion of the project.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id80b85d28-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3307/j"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"j"},"text":"(j)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Expiration of Committee Resolutions.—","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id80b85d29-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3307/j/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"In general","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"Unless a lease is awarded or a construction, alteration, repair, design, or acquisition project is initiated not later than 5 years after the resolution approvals adopted by the Committee on Transportation and Infrastructure of the House of Representatives and the Committee on Environment and Public Works of the Senate pursuant to subsection (a), the resolutions shall be deemed expired.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id80b85d2a-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s3307/j/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Application","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"This subsection shall only apply to resolutions approved after the date of enactment of this subsection.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id80b85d2b-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/217"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–217","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-08-21"},"text":"Aug. 21, 2002","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/116/1161"},"text":"116 Stat. 1161","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/140/tIII/s323/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–140, title III, § 323(a)","children":[],"tail":", (b), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2007-12-19"},"text":"Dec. 19, 2007","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/121/1589"},"text":"121 Stat. 1589","children":[],"tail":", 1590; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/287/s17"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–287, § 17","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2016-12-16"},"text":"Dec. 16, 2016","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/130/1476"},"text":"130 Stat. 1476","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/118/272/dB/tIII"},"text":"Pub. L. 118–272, div. B, title III","children":[],"tail":", §§ 2304(a), (c), (f), 2310, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2025-01-04"},"text":"Jan. 4, 2025","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/138/3223"},"text":"138 Stat. 3223","children":[],"tail":", 3224, 3227.)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id80b85d2c-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"id80b85d2d-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:table","attrib":{"width":"50%","id":"id80b85d2e-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:colgroup","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children"